oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Real picture postcard of Jeff Warricks in uniform
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: In this photograph, a soldier, possibly Jeff Warricks of Maryville, posed in uniform holding a 1903 Springfield rifle. Warricks enlisted at age 18 and served as a bugler in Co. B, 117th Inf. Regt. Div. during World War I. He was overseas from May 11, 1918 until March 27, 1919.
